datoCmsKey.name: Liz Neitge
datoCmsKey.bio:
Liz Neitge received her Bachelor of Music in Musical Theatre Performance from Arizona State University. She is now happily Brooklyn-based.

Originally from Minnesota and adopted at birth with her twin brother. Proudly queer and Latinx.

Liz recently returned to NYC after performing in the new play Chatoâ€™s Kitchen with Childsplay in Arizona, a collaboration with the NJ Performing Arts Center. Other recent regional credits include West Side Story (Seacoast Repertory), Ghost the Musical (The Winnipesaukee Playhouse) and The Velveteen Rabbit (Jenny Wiley Theatre).
